Package commands

package commands
  • Class
    Description
    AbstractCommand
    An abstract class that implements the Command interface and provides basic functionality for all commands.
    AddElement
    The AddElement class represents a command that adds a new worker element to the collection.
    AddElementIfMin
    The AddElementIfMin class represents a command that adds a new worker element to the collection if its salary is less than the salary of all the elements in the collection.
    Clear
    The Clear class represents a command that clears the collection.
    Command
     
    ExecuteScript
    The ExecuteScript class represents a command to execute a script file.
    Exit
    The Exit class extends the AbstractCommand class and represents a command that terminates the program.
    FilterGreaterStatus
    The FilterGreaterStatus class represents a command that filters the elements in the collection by the status field and displays those whose value is greater than the specified one.
    GroupByStatus
    This command groups the elements of the collection by the value of the status field and displays the number of elements in each group.
    Help
    The Help command displays the list of available commands and their descriptions.
    Info
    Command to display information about the collection.
    PrintFieldOfPerson
    Command to print the Person data in ascending order by their name.
    RemoveElementByID
    The RemoveElementByID class represents a command to remove an element from the collection by its ID.
    RemoveGreater
    The RemoveGreater class represents a command to remove all elements from the collection that are greater than the specified element.
    SaveCollection
    The Show class represents a command that outputs all elements of the collection in string representation.
    Show
    Command
    Sort
    The Sort class represents a command to sort the collection in natural order.
    UpdateByID
    This command is used to update the value of a collection element whose id matches the specified one.
